<paragraph id="AA0B3684FFD9F6263BE9FA4CFDEDF940" blockId="6.[151,1437,1505,1711]" pageId="6" pageNumber="349">
The 
<typeStatus id="750F8826FFD9F6263BB4FA4CFF1CFA14" box="[202,250,1505,1531]" pageId="6" pageNumber="349">type</typeStatus>
specimen of this little known species has not been detected in L. Beguin-Billecocq’s collection at MNHN by the senior author. No other material was available for this study, except for the image by Harry Taylor (BMNH) published at ‘Beetles of Mauritius’ website http://mauritiusbeetles.myspecies.info/gallery?page=6 (
<bibRefCitation id="CE254B75FFD9F6263E7CF984FF35F988" accessDate="2019-02-12" author="Motala, S. &amp; Krell, F. - T. &amp; Barclay, M. V. L. &amp; Mendel, H. &amp; Baker, E." etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Motala" journalOrPublisher="Hosted by Natural History Museum, London and Mauritian Wildlife Foundation" pageId="6" pageNumber="349" publicationUrl="http://mauritiusbeetles.myspecies.info/" refId="ref4168" refString="Motala, S., Krell, F. - T., Barclay, M. V. L., Mendel, H. &amp; Baker, E. (2009) Beetles of Mauritius website. Hosted by Natural History Museum, London and Mauritian Wildlife Foundation http: // mauritiusbeetles. myspecies. info / (accessed 12 February 2019)" title="Beetles of Mauritius website" type="url" year="2009">
Motala 
<emphasis id="98C0EA96FFD9F6263E24F987FA68F9AC" box="[1370,1422,1577,1603]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="349">et al</emphasis>
., 2009
</bibRefCitation>
), allowing for unambiguous placement of this species in the genus 
<emphasis id="98C0EA96FFD9F62638B1F9E3FB82F988" box="[975,1124,1614,1639]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="349">Mascarapion</emphasis>
. It is at first glance distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="6DB44D07FFD9F6263BA9F9DFFEBCF964" authorityName="Richard" authorityYear="1957" box="[215,346,1649,1675]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roudieri">
<emphasis id="98C0EA96FFD9F6263BA9F9DFFF08F964" box="[215,238,1650,1675]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="349">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="98C0EA96FFD9F6263B81F9DCFEBCF964" box="[255,346,1649,1675]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="349">roudieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6DB44D07FFD9F6263AEBF9DFFDFEF964" authorityName="Wanat &amp; Poussereau" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Alonso-Zarazaga" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[405,536,1649,1675]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Mascarapion" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="349" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="richardi">
<emphasis id="98C0EA96FFD9F6263AEBF9DFFDFEF964" box="[405,536,1649,1675]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="349">M. richardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having tri-colored vestiture on the elytra, with pure white scales forming a small, isolated postscutellar spot.
</paragraph>
